history.content:
CS170: Useful for interviews. Can be difficult if you struggled with both 61B and 70. Otherwise, HW's and exams are more long than they are hard.
CS189: Useful if you're a frequent Kaggle user. Can be difficult if you struggled with 54. Little relation to 53 or 188. Good prep for a grad-level ML course. 

-------------------------------------

170: Little to no coding aside from the final project. The psets, however, require you come up with some of "trick" to solve and at times feel like a puzzle.

189: Less of the trick and puzzle aspect of 170, so a bit more straightforward in that regard, but is MUCH more coding and math heavy. I personally find 170 harder but each will have their own strengths and weaknesses which will make this answer vary alot.

CS170: Useful for interviews. Can be difficult if you struggled with both 61B and 70. Otherwise, HW's and exams are more long than they are hard.
CS189: Useful if you're a frequent Kaggle user. Can be difficult if you struggled with 54. Little relation to 53 or 188. Good prep for a grad-level ML course.

children.subject: At least for me 189 was significantly more difficult than 170, although I did take 189 concurrently with 188 (but I don't think that is a huge deal). 170 is useful for everybody, as it gets you thinking in lots of new ways while problem-solving (yes, also helpful for interviews); 189 is extremely helpful for those interested in going into AI/ML, but less useful for the average computer scientist just looking to learn a thing or two, as it really gets down into the mathematical minutia. I would recommend both.

history.content: Which is more difficult? Which is more useful?
history.subject: cs170 or cs189
